Ed,<br><br>
Your entry about the St Christopher's medal and you father's tears reminded me of my own father's tears the night before I was inducted. He told me, &quot;Don't betray your country.&quot;<br><br>
Many times I have pondered those words, and honestly don't feel as if those who protested were betrayers - as long as they were motivated by their *consciences*. Accountability to a belief in God takes preference over country, in my opinion.<br><br>
Having said this, I want to tell you that I appreciate your sacrifice, and consider it a privilege to know you. Nothing anyone could ever say could ever take away from what you have accomplished and survived.<br><br>
God bless you.
<p><code>-- wingman@greene8xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


